description: Wellington Frick, a playboy on his last financial legs, leads a team of scavengers to investigate an unexplored pyramid on a distant world that promises a king's ransom in richesâ€”including priceless Alien eggs. Bringing along only a synthetic, a videographer, and the only man ever to survive a chestburster, Frick soon discovers that the pyramid has indeed been visited before, but the explorers never left. And dead explorers and breached Alien eggs mean that the team's quest for fame and fortune has become a fight for survival.

Big Man, by knee-capping a guy with a drywall hatchet, begins his bloody road of revenge as more clues to his mysterious motivations are revealed.

Legendary comic book artist Sam Glanzman draws upon his own experiences aboard a WWII destroyer in these gripping tales of Navy life, including a new 10-page story and a new foreword by New York Times-bestselling author of World War Z, Max Brooks. Recounted in graphic novel style, these dramatic adventures realistically depict a teenager's military career, from initiation and advancement through the ranks to tours of the Pacific and kamikaze attacks at the Battle of Okinawa.

description:
Welcome to Kaijumax, where the worst of the worst monsters are safely locked away from the human world, whether they be villains, anti-heroes, eco-parables, or nuclear metaphors. Electrogor is ripped away from his family and struggles to determine whom to trust, which gangs to avoid, and when to take on the big man to show you aren't to be trifled with. Also: the nation of Mecha!
